\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}For my husband is not at home;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he is far away on a journey.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}He has taken a money-bag with him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he will not come home till full moon.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}With her fair speech she beguiled him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with her blandishing words she enticed him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}So he followed her bewitched,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
like an ox that is brought to the slaughter,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like a dog that is led on a chain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}like a bird rushing into a net,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
unaware that its life is at stake,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
till an arrow pierces its liver.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And now, my son, listen to me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Give heed to the words that I utter.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Let your heart not swerve to her ways,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and wander not in her paths;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}for the dead she has cast down are many,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and many are those she has slain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Her house is the road to Sheol,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
straight down to the chambers of Death.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Invitation and the Rewards of Wisdom

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Wisdom\uc1\u8217*s Appeal to Men}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}Listen! Wisdom is calling,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and Reason is lifting her voice:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}on a raised place, high by the way.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
on the streets she has taken her stand.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}By the gates that lead into the city.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
She cries aloud at the portals:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*to you, O men, I call.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And my voice is to all mankind.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}You simple ones, learn to be prudent;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
You foolish ones, get to know wisdom.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}O listen, for grave is my message.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And right all the speech of my lips.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}It is truth that my mouth discourses,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And falsehood my lips abhor.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}All the words that I utter are honest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Free from all that is crooked and tortuous,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}All clear to the man of sense,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and right to those that have knowledge.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Choose instruction, then, rather than silver,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and more than choice gold welcome knowledge.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For better is Wisdom than corals;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
no treasures with her can compare.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I, Wisdom, possess intelligence;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
knowledge and insight are mine.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Mine are counsel and skill;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
understanding and might are mine.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}By me do monarchs reign
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and rulers administer justice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}By me do princes govern
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and noblemen rule the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Those that love me I love,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and those that seek me find me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}With me are riches and honour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
prosperity and grandeur.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}My fruit is better than finest gold,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
my revenue fairer than choicest silver.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}I walk in the way that is fair,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and keep to the paths of justice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}endowing with wealth those that love me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and filling their treasuries full.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Wisdom\uc1\u8217*s Ancient Origin}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}At the very beginning God fashioned me
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
as the first of His works of old.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}In the ancient time was I formed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
at the first, when the world began.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}I was born when as yet no depths were,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
no fountains laden with water;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Ere yet the mountains were sunk,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and before the hills was I born;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Ere the earth and the fields were created,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or the first of the clods of the world.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}When He set up the heavens, I was there;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
when He vaulted the face of the deep;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}When He made firm the skies above,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and fixed the deep fast at its sources;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}When He set to the sea its bounds,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
as He marked off the base of the world.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Then beside Him was I as His nursling,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I was His daily delight,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
playing before Him at all times,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}playing about in His world.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
delighting in humankind.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Wisdom\uc1\u8217*s Concluding Appeal}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}And now, children, listen to me:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
happy those that keep to my ways.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Hear instruction, and thus get wisdom.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Do not reject my admonition.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Happy he who listens to me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
daily watching at my gates,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and waiting at my door-posts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}For who finds me finds life,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he wins the Lord\uc1\u8217*s own favour;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}but who misses me wrongs himself,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for all that hate me love death.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Two Hostesses \uc1\u8211* Wisdom and Folly

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i The Invitation of Wisdom}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}Wisdom has built her a house,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
has set up her seven pillars,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}slain her beasts, and mingled her wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and also spread her table.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}She has sent forth her maidens to cry
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
on the thoroughfares of the city:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*All simple ones, turn in hither,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I would speak to him who lacks wisdom.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Come and eat of my bread.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and drink of the wine I have mingled,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Abandon your folly, and live,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and walk in the way of reason.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Who corrects a scoffer but gets himself insult,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a stain rests on him that reproves the wicked.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Reprove not a scoffer, or else he may hate you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a wise man reprove, and for that he will love you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Give to a wise man, and he will grow wiser;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
instruct the righteous, and more he will learn.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The fear of the Lord is the first step to wisdom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and to know the Holy One is understanding.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For by me your days will be many,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the years of your life increased.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}If you are wise, you are wise for yourself;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And if you scoff, you must bear it alone.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i The Invitation of Folly}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Dame Folly is loud and seductive,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
she is a stranger to shame.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}At the door of her house she sits,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
on the thoroughfares of the city,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}calling to passers-by,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who are going straight on their way:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*All simple ones, turn in hither,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I would speak to him who lacks wisdom.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Stolen waters are sweet,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But he does not know that dead men are there,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
that her guests lie sunken in Sheol.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Warnings

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Against Suretyship}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}My son if you have gone bail for your neighbour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and given your pledge for another;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}if by your own lips you are snared,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and are trapped by the words of your mouth:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}then this do, my son, and free yourself,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
since you have come into his power.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Go, stir youself, besiege your neighbour;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}give no sleep to your eyes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor slumber to your eyelids,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}shake yourself free, like a roe, from the snare,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or a bird from the hand of the fowler.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Against Indolence}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Go to the ant, you sluggard;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
consider her ways, and be wise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}without officer, ruler, or chief,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}she provides her bread in the summer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and gathers her food in the harvest.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}How long will you lie, O sluggard?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
When will you rise from your sleep?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*Just a little more sleep, a little more slumber,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a little more lying with folded hands.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}So will poverty come on you like a robber,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and want like an armed man.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Against Underhand Mischief-making}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Sunk in wickedness is the man
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
whose speech is ingrained with falsehood \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}who winks his eyes,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or shuffles his feet,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or makes signs with his fingers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}gives his mind to the planning of mischief,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and always is scattering discord.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For these things will sudden disaster assail him;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he will swiftly be crushed beyond all hope of healing.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Seven Detestable Things}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Six things there are which the Lord detests,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
yes, seven does He abhor:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}haughty eyes, a lying tongue,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and hands that shed innocent blood,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}a mind that plans wicked devices,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and feet that are swift to do wrong,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}a false witness that utters lies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
One that scatters strife among brethren.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 First Collection of Proverbs

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}The Proverbs of Solomon:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
A wise son makes his father glad,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a foolish son is a grief to his mother.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Treasures wrongly acquired profit nothing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but righteousness saves from death.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The Lord will not suffer the righteous to hunger,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but He will frustrate the desire of the wicked.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}A slack hand creates poverty,
\par}

