\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The prudent scent mischief and hide;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the simple go on and are punished.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The reward of the humble who fear the Lord
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is riches and honour and life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}On the way of the crooked lie traps and snares;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he who watches his life will keep far away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Train up a child for his destined way,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and, even when old, he will not depart from it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The rich lords it over the poor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the borrower is slave to the lender.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He that sows wrong will reap trouble,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the gain he has toiled for will vanish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The man with the kindly eye will be blessed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for he gives of his bread to the poor.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Expel the scoffer and discord will vanish,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and strife and insult cease.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The pure in heart are beloved of the Lord,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the winsome of speech have the king for a friend.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The Lord is watching, alert and aware,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nd the aims of the false he subverts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}The lazy man says, \uc1\u8220*There\uc1\u8217*s a lion outside.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
on the street I am like to be murdered.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}The lewd woman\uc1\u8217*s mouth is a deep, deep pit;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he who angers the Lord will fall into it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Folly is bound to the mind of a child,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the rod of correction removes it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}He who crushes the poor in the end but enriches him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a gift to the rich only tends to his poverty.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Second Collection of Proverbs

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 22}Incline your ear and hear my words,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and set your heart to know their beauty.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Keep them in your mind,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
have them ever fixed on your lips.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}That your trust may be in the Lord
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I teach you them this day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}As I wrote for you heretofore
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
concerning counsels of wisdom \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}to acquaint you with words of truth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and with answers for those who would question you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Rob not the poor because he is poor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and crush not the weak in the gate;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}For the Lord will defend their cause,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and will rob of their lives those who rob them.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Make no friend of a man prone to anger,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor go with a man of passion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}in case you learn his ways.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and get yourself ensnared.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Be not one of those that give pledges,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
of those that are surety for debt;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}for if you have nothing to pay,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
your bed will be taken from under you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Remove not the ancient landmark
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
established by your fathers.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Do you see a man expert in his business?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He will stand in the presence of kings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but before obscure men he will not stand.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 23}If you sit at a ruler\uc1\u8217*s table,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
consider well who is before you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and set a knife to your throat,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
if you be a hearty eater.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Toil not to make yourself rich,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
desist from this your purpose;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}for no sooner seen than gone.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
For riches make themselves wings
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
like an eagle that flies towards heaven.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Do not dine with a niggardly man,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and do not fancy his dainties;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}for a reckoning soul has he.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He tells you to eat and drink,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but his heart is not with yours.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}You must spit out the piece you have eaten,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for it is bread of deceit.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Speak not in the ears of a fool.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
For your wisest words he despises \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
your fair discourse is in vain.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Remove not the widow\uc1\u8217*s landmark,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor enter the fields of the fatherless;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}for they have a mighty champion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who will plead their cause against you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Apply your mind to instruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
your ear to the words of knowledge.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Leave not a child unchastised,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for your beating will save him from death.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It is for you to beat him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and so will you save him from Sheol.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}My son, if your heart be wise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
then my heart too will be glad.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I will rejoice from my soul,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
when your lips utter words of rectitude.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Be not envious of sinners,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but ever fear the Lord;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}for there is a future for you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and your hope will not be cut off.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Listen, my son, and be wise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and walk in the way of prudence.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Mix not with men that drink wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or that gorge themselves with flesh;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}for gorging and drink make men paupers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and drowsiness covers with rags.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Listen to the father that begat you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and despise not your aged mother;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For a righteous son makes a glad, glad father,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a prudent son is the joy of his mother.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But let your father be glad,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and make your mother happy.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Give heed to me, my son.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Let your eyes take note of my ways.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}For a deep, deep pit is the harlot,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the lewd woman a narrow well.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}She lies in wait like a robber,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and many are they she plunders.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i The Peril of Wine}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Who is it that cries, \uc1\u8220*Ah! Woe is me!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who is it that has quarrels and plaints?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who is it that has senseless bruises?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
And who has the dull red eyes?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Those that linger over wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
those that drink spiced wine with a relish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Look not on the ruddy wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
when in the cup it sparkles,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
smoothly it glides down;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}but at last it bites like a serpent,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and stings like an adder.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Strange things your eyes behold,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
your mind and your speech go a-wandering;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Like one riding the sea are you
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the throes of a violent storm.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}I was struck, but I feel no pain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
of the blows I am all unconscious.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
O when will I wake from my wine?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I would seek it once again.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 24}Be not envious of evil men,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and do not desire to be with them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}for they cherish designs of plunder,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and mischief is on their lips.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}By wisdom a house is built up,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
by intelligence it is established;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}by knowledge its shambers are filled
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with all precious and pleasant substance.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Wise men are better than strong men,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and knowledge is better than might;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}for wars are waged by wise guidance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and victory lies in counsellors.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Wisdom is too high for a fool;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so he opens not his mouth in the gate.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The man who deviseth mischief
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is known among men as a schemer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The scheming of fools is sin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the scoffer is hated of men.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}If you have been slack, in the day of distress
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
your resource will be scanty.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Rescue those that are taken to death;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
save those that are tottering to slaughter.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}If you say, \uc1\u8220*It is not in my power,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he who weighs the heart, he discerns;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He who watches your soul, he knows,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and on each he will bring back his deeds.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}As the honey you eat, my son, is wholesome.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and sweet to your taste is the honeycomb,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}even so, be assured, to your soul is wisdom.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Lie not in wait for the home of the just,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and do not assail his dwelling-place;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}for the just, though he fall seven times, will rise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the wicked will stumble to ruin.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}At the fall of your foe rejoice not,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and do not exult at his overthrow;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}lest the Lord be displeased when he sees it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and turn His anger away from him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Be not fretful because of evildoers.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor envious of the wicked;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}for the bad man will have no future.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The lamp of the wicked is quenched.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Fear the Lord, my son, and the king,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
be not haughty to one or the other;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}for swift is the ruin they raise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the disaster they send unforeseen.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Appendix to the Second Collection of Proverbs

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}These also belong to the wise men:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
It is wrong to be partial in giving of judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}All men will curse and all people will execrate
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
him who pronounces the guilty man innocent.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But those whose decisions are just will fare pleasantly;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
blessings of fortune will rest upon them.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}As one who kisses the lips
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is he who returns a straight answer.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Set your business in order without,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
make all ready in your fields:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
after that you may build up your house.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Bear not false witness against your neighbour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor let your lips be deceitful.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Do not threaten to treat him as he treated you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and to visit his deed with retribution.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i On the Sluggard}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}By the field of the sluggard I passed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
by the vineyard of one that was foolish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}It was all overgrown with thistles;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
its surface was covered with nettles;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
its wall of stone was in ruins.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}As I looked, I thought upon it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I drew from the sight a lesson.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8220*Just a little more sleep, a little more slumber,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a little more lying with folded hands.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}So will poverty come upon you like a robber,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and want like an armed man.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Third Collection of Proverbs

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 25}These also are proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah, king of Judah, copied out.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The glory of God is his mystery,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the glory of kings is investigation.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Like the height of the heavens and the depth of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so the purpose of kings is unsearchable.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Remove the dross from silver,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and forth it comes pure altogether.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Remove wicked men from the king.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and his throne is established by righteousness.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}In the presence of a king claim not honour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor stand in the place of the great.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Better be told, \uc1\u8220*Come up hither,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
than be humbled before the prince.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Do not hastily bring up a law-suit
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
of something your eyes have seen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For what will you do in the end,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
when your neighbour has put you to shame?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Discuss the affair with your neighbour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
reveal not his secret to others;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}lest those that have heard it reproach you
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and your infamy pass not away.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Like apples of gold in carvings of silver
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a word that is fittingly spoken.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Like an earring of gold and a necklace of fine gold
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a wise man\uc1\u8217*s reproof to a listening ear.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Like a drink cooled by snow in the time of harvest
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a faithful envoy to those that send him:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he refreshes the soul of his master.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}As clouds and wind that yet bring no rain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so is one that boasts of gifts that he gives not.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}An angry man can be won by forbearance,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and bones can be broken by gentle words.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}If you find honey, eat just what you need.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
lest, after a surfeit, you vomit it up.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}In the house of your friend let your foot be but seldom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
lest, sated with you, he detest you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}One who bears false witness against his neighbour
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a hammer, a sword, and a sharp-pointed arrow.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}In a crumbling tooth and a foot unsteady
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is the faithless man\uc1\u8217*s trust in the day of distress.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}As vinegar to a wound
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a song to a sorrowful heart.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Give your enemy food, if he hunger;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and water, if he be thirsty:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}for so will you heap coals of fire on his head,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the Lord will give you recompense.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}As the north wind brings forth rain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so slander an angry countenance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}It is better to live on the roof in a corner
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
than in a spacious house with a quarrelsome woman.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Like cool water to one that is weary
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is good news from a distant land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Like a fountain befouled or a ruined spring
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a just man who falls before the wicked.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}It is not good to eat much honey;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
be sparing then of your compliments.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Like a city whose walls are broken down
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a man without self-control.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 26}In a fool is honour as unbecoming
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
as snow in summer or rain in harvest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Like the aimless flight of a sparrow or swallow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the curse that is baseless does not come home.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}A whip for the horse, a bridle for the ass,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a rod for the back of fools.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Do not answer a fool as beseems his folly,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in case you, too, become like him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Answer a fool as beseems his folly,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
lest he fancy himself to be wise.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}To send a fool with a message
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is to cut off one\uc1\u8217*s feet and to drink disaster.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Like the limp legs of the lame
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a proverb in the mouth of a fool.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Like a bundle of jewels on a heap of stones
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is honour conferred on a fool.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Like a thorn-stick brandished by a drunken man
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a proverb in the mouth of a fool.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}All fools must suffer sore anguish of body.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and their insolence will be shattered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Like a dog that returns to his vomit,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a fool repeats his folly.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}If you see a man who thinks himself wise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
there is far more hope for a fool than for him.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i On the Sluggard}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}The lazy man saith, \uc1\u8220*There\uc1\u8217*s a lion on the road,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
there\uc1\u8217*s a lion on the street.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}As the door turns on its hinges,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so the lazy man in his bed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}The lazy man buries his hand in the dish \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
too weary to carry it back to his mouth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The lazy man thinks himself wiser
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
than seven who can answer discreetly.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}To mix in a quarrel not your own
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is to catch a dog by the ears.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Like a madman who hurls about
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
deadly fire-brands and arrows,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}is the man who deceives his neighbour
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and says that he did it in jest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}In the absence of wood the fire goes out.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
In the absence of slander contention ceases.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}As charcoal to embers or wood to fire
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a quarrelsome man for kindling strife.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Slanderous words are like dainty morsels,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
down they glide to the innermost being.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i On Hypocrisy}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Like a sherd overlaid with silver slag
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a wicked heart with glowing lips.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}With his lips one who hates you dissembles.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but he cherishes guile in his heart.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}When he speaks you fair, trust him not:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in his heart lurk hateful things seven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}He who digs a pit will fall into it;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he who rolls a stone gets it back upon him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}A false tongue brings destruction;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a flattering mouth works ruin.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}One who veils his hatred with guile
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
has his malice uncovered in public.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 27}Boast not yourself of tomorrow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for you do not know what a day may bring forth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Let another mouth praise you, not yours \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the lips of some other, not yours.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}A stone is heavy and sand is weighty,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but heavier than both the vexation caused by fools.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Indignation is fierce, anger pours like a flood;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but who can stand before jealousy?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Better an open reproof
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
than affection that is concealed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The wounds of a friend are sincere,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but profuse are the kisses of a foe.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Honey is scorned by a man that is full,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but anything bitter is sweet to the hungry.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Like a bird that strays from its nest
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a man that wanders from home.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Oil and perfume rejoice the heart,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but sorrow of spirit does rend it asunder.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Your friend and your father\uc1\u8217*s friend forsake not;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and in your day of distress
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
do not enter the house of your brother,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
near neighbour is better than distant brother.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Be wise, my son, and gladden my heart.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
that so I may answer the man who would taunt me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The prudent scent mischief and hide;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the simple go on and are punished.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Take the garment of him who goes bail for another,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and hold it in pledge for that other.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}If early in the morning
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
one loudly blesses another,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
it is reckoned to him as a curse.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}An endless drip on a rainy day
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a quarrelsome wife are alike;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}he hides the wind that would hide her,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and his hand grasps at oil.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}As iron sharpens iron,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so a man sharpens his friend.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}He that tends a fig tree will eat its fruit;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so one who attends to his lord will get honour.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}As face answers to face
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so the mind of one man to another.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Abaddon and Sheol are ever unsated.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and ever unsated the eyes of men.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}As the smelter for silver, the furnace for gold,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so repute is the test of a man.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Though you bray a fool with a pestle
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
along with bruised grain in a mortar.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
you will not get him rid of his folly.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs24 {\i Advice to Farmers}

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Look well to the state of your flock,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and give your mind to your herds;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For wealth lasts not forever,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor riches through all generations.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}When the hay is removed and the new growth appears,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the grass of the uplands is all gathered in,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Then the lambs will supply you with clothing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the goats with the price of a field;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}goats\uc1\u8217* milk enough there will be for your food,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a livelihood for your slave-girls.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 28}The wicked flee, when no man pursues,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the righteous are bold as a lion.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}By the sin of the violent quarrels arise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a man of sense will extinguish them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}A wicked man that oppresses the poor
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a deluging rain that leaves no food.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Those who turn from instruction admire the wicked,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but those who observe it are zealous against them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The wicked have no understanding of justice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but who cares for the Lord understands it completely.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Better a poor man whose life is blameless
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
than one who is crooked, although he be rich.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}A son that is prudent observes instruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the comrade of profligates shames his father.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He that adds to his substance by interest or increase
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but gathers for him that is kind to the poor.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}If one turns a deaf ear to instruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
his very prayers are detestable.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He that turns the upright to wicked ways
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
will himself fall into the pit that he dug;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the blameless will come to prosperity.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}A rich man may think himself wise,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a poor man with brains can see through him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}What a pageant there is, when the just are triumphant!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
When the wicked emerge into power, men hide.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}No man will prosper that covers his sins,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but those that confess and forsake them find mercy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Happy the man who fears always,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the obstinate plunge to disaster.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}A roaring lion, a prowling bear,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is a bad man who rules an impoverished people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}That prince has no prudence that plays the oppressor.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but long will he live that detests unjust gain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}He who sheds the blood of a man \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
let him flee to a city, let none apprehend him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The blameless life will be kept in safety,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the crooked life will suddenly fall.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}He that tills his land will have plenty of bread.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but idle pursuits end in plenty of poverty.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}A trustworthy man will be richly blessed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but who hastes to get riches will not go unpunished.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}It is wrong for a man to be partial,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to sin for a piece of bread.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}A greedy man hastes to be rich,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
not knowing that want will befall him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}A man who reproves gets more thanks in the end
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
than a smooth-tongued flatterer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}One who robs his parents and says, \uc1\u8220*It is no sin,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is companion to him who destroys.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}A greedy man stirs up strife;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he who trusts in the Lord will flourish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}He who trusts in himself is a fool;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he who walks in wisdom is safe.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}He who gives to the poor will not come to want,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but who veileth his eyes will have many a curse.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}When the wicked emerge into power, men hide;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
when they perish, the righteous increase.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 29}One who stiffens his neck against all reproof
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
will be suddenly crushed beyond healing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}When the just are in power, the people are glad;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
when the wicked hold sway, the people groan.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}A man who loves wisdom brings joy to his father,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the comrade of harlots consumes his substance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}By justice a king sets his country erect,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but one whose exactions are heavy destroys it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}A man who cajols his neighbour
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is spreading a net for his steps.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}By his sin is a wicked man snared,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the righteous does shout for joy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}To the righteous the cause of the poor is dear,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the wicked care nothing at all.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Scoffers inflame a city (with discord),
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but wise men turn passions aside.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}When a wise man disputes with a fool,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he storms and laughs, and peace there is none.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Men of blood hate the blameless;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the wicked seek for his life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The fool lets his temper go,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a wise man restrains his anger.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}If a ruler pays heed to false tales,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
his officials all grow to be scoundrels.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Oppressor and poor meet together,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the light in the eyes of them both is the Lord\uc1\u8217*s.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}If a king be faithful and just to the poor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
his throne will stand forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}The rod of correction brings wisdom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a child let loose brings disgrace on his mother.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}When the wicked hold sway, wrong increases,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the righteous will gloat on their downfall.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Correct your son and your mind will be eased,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and he will delight your soul.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}People break loose in the absence of vision,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but he who observes instruction is happy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Not by words can a servant be trained;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for he knows, but he will not obey.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}See you a man of hasty speech,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
there is far more hope for a fool than for him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The spoiled child will end as a servant,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and come to grief at the last.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}A passionate man stirs up strife,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and much evil is wrought by hot temper.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Pride will lay a man low,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but the lowly attain to honour.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}His own foe is he who goes shares with a thief;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he hears the curse, but he utters nothing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}The fear of man brings a snare,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but who trusts the Lord is safe.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Many seek royal favour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but it is God who decides every man\uc1\u8217*s fate.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The righteous abhor the unjust,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the wicked abhor the upright.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Collection of Brief Discourses and Aphorisms

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 30}The words of Agur, son of Jakeh, the Massaite. Oracle of the man.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Weary World-Problem

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I have wearied myself, O God;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
O God, I am weary and spent:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For dull as a brute am I,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
not a man with the mind of a man.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}I have not learned wisdom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and nothing I know of the Holy One.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Who has climbed the heavens and come down?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Who has gathered the wind in his fist?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Who has tied in a garment the waters,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or set up the bounds of the earth?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
What is his name, or his son\uc1\u8217*s name?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for surely you know.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The words of God have all been tested,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he shields those who take refuge in him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}To his words add you nothing at all,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
lest He should convict you of being a liar.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 A Prayer for Preservation alike from Wealth and Poverty

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For two things I entreat you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
deny me not, before I die.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Put falseness and lying away from me;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
give me neither riches nor poverty,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
grant me the food I need;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}lest, if surfeited, I deny you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and say, \uc1\u8220*Who then is the Lord?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Or poverty drive me to steal,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and profane the name of my God.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Against Defamation

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}To a master defame not his servant,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
lest he curse you and you have to smart for it.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Four Evil Types

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}There are those who curse their fathers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and leave their mothers unblessed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}There are others that think themselves pure,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
yet are all unwashed of their filthiness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}There are others with haughty eyes
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and supercilious eyebrows.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}There are others whose teeth are swords \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the teeth in their jaws are knives,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to devour the poor from the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the needy from off the ground.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Four Insatiable Things

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}There are three things that never are satisfied \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
four that say never, \uc1\u8220*Enough!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Sheol; the womb that is barren;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the earth unsated with water;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and fire that says never, \uc1\u8220*Enough!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Against Contempt of Parents

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}The eye that mocks a father,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and scornes an aged mother,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will be picked by the crows of the valley
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and clean devoured by vultures.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Four Mysterious Things

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Three things are too wonderful for me \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
four are beyond my knowledge:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}the way of a vulture in air,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the way of a snake on a rock,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the way of a ship on the sea,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the way of a man with a woman.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Four Intolerable Things

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Under three things the earth does tremble \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
four she cannot bear:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}A slave when he comes to the throne,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a fool who has more than enough,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}a plain woman when she gets married,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a maid that is heir to her mistress.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Four Things Little but Wise

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Of the small things of earth there are four.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and wiser they are than the wisest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}The ants are a feeble folk,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
yet they lay up their food in the summer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}A feeble folk, too, are the conies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
yet they make their house in the rocks.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}The locusts again, though kingless,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
yet march, every one, in good order.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And a lizard you could crush in your hand
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
finds her way into royal palaces.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Four Stately Things

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Three creatures there are whose step is stately,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
four whose step is majestic \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}The lion, most valiant of beasts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who in presence of foe never flinches;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}The proud strutting cock and the he-goat,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a king who is head of his army.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Bluster you not in arrogance,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but lay your hand on your mouth.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}As the churning of milk yields curd,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the wringing of the nose yields blood,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so the churning of wrath yields strife.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Against Immorality and Intemperance

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 31}The words of Lemuel, king of Massa, which his mother taught him.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}O son whom I bore, give heed to my words;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and observe my sayings, you son of my vows.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Give not your strength to women,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor your love to those that slay kings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Nor for kings is it right to drink wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
or for princes to long for strong drink;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Lest in drink they forget the law,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and do wrong to the cause of the sorrowful.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But give drink to him who is perishing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and wine to the bitter in soul;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}so that in drink he forget his poverty,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and think of his sorrow no more.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Open your mouth for the widow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
do right by all fatherless children.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Open your mouth in just judgment.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
defend the poor and the needy.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Ideal Housewife

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}A woman of worth who can find?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Her price is far above corals.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}To her her husband trusts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and finds no lack of gain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}She does him good and not harm
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all the days of his life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}She looks out wool and flax.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and works it up as she will.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Like the merchant-ships is she;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
she brings her food from afar.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}She rises while yet it is night,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and gives her household food,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and her maidens their portion appointed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}She examines a field and buys it;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with her earnings she plants a vineyard,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}She girds her loins with strength,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and with vigour she plies her arms.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}She perceives that her profit is good;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
her lamp never goes out in the night.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}She lays her hand on the distaff;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
her hand takes hold of the spindle.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}She stretches her hand to the poor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and her hand she extends to the needy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}She fears not the snow for her household;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
her household are all clad in scarlet.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And coverlets she has made her;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
her raiment is linen and purple.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}In the gates is her husband well known,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
where he sits with the elders in council.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Linen she makes and sells;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to the merchant she furnishes girdles.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}She is clothed with strength and glory;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
she laughs at the days to come.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Her mouth she opens in wisdom;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
kind counsel is on her tongue.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}She looks well to the ways of her household;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
she eats not the bread of idleness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Her children arise and bless her;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
her husband sings her praises:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8220*Many daughters have done nobly,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but you excellest them all!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Grace is deceptive, and beauty is transient.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but a woman of character \uc1\u8211* she will be praised.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Give her then what her hands have earned,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
even the praise of her deeds in the gates.
\par}

